{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V3KKbKE9P9hzSVCBt1jf9B","type":"tool_result","content":"33-- FR15: System can load existing workflows without driver/model fields with full backward compatibility\n34:- FR16: System can execute a workflow where consecutive tasks use different drivers\n35:- FR17: System can serialize a task's output contract to a structured JSON file after task completion\n36:- FR18: System can load a previous task's output contract and inject it as context into the next task's prompt\n37:- FR19: System can pass acceptance criteria, changed file lists, and test results across framework boundaries via output contracts\n38:- FR20: System can execute verification tasks on a different framework than implementation tasks within the same story\n39-- FR21: User can configure gstack skills to load within claude-code driver sessions via workflow or agent config\n--\n74-- NFR15: Output contract files must survive engine crashes — written atomically\n75:- NFR16: Driver timeout must be configurable per task (default: 30 minutes)\n76:- NFR17: TUI must remain responsive during driver failures\n77:- NFR18: Workflow engine must be idempotent for re-runs — resume from last completed task\n78-\n--\n109-| FR15 | Epic 1, 2 | Backward compatibility for old workflows |\n110:| FR16 | Epic 4 | Execute workflow with different drivers per task |\n111:| FR17 | Epic 4 | Serialize output contract to JSON |\n112:| FR18 | Epic 4 | Load and inject output contract into next task |\n113:| FR19 | Epic 4 | Pass ACs, files, tests across framework boundaries |\n114:| FR20 | Epic 4 | Verification on different framework than implementation |\n115-| FR21 | Epic 6 | Configure gstack skills in claude-code sessions |\n--\n149-Users can run workflows where consecutive tasks use different frameworks, with output contracts passing context between them. Cross-framework verification works end-to-end.\n150:**FRs covered:** FR16, FR17, FR18, FR19, FR20\n151-\n--\n384-**And** loop blocks correctly alternate between drivers\n385:**And** the workflow engine resumes from the last completed task on re-run (NFR18)\n386-\n--\n435-**And** per-story cost breakdown shows cost by driver\n436:**And** the TUI remains responsive during driver failures (NFR17)\n437-"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019LUaUpkJKAsHhoTwURUxyL","session_id":"d2473842-56c4-49f2-ab43-68fabe9113bb","uuid":"a06d5a53-7012-4e40-aeb8-059f96a0f7a6","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:46:48.981Z"}
