{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019LUaUpkJKAsHhoTwURUxyL","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-3-cross-framework-workflow-execution.md`.\n\n**Summary:** Created story 13-3 (Cross-Framework Workflow Execution) — the last story in Epic 13. It wires together the output contract write/read (13-1) and prompt injection (13-2) into the workflow engine's execution flow. 10 acceptance criteria, 8 tasks. All ACs tagged `test-provable` because they can be verified via build + unit tests with mocked drivers (no running app or environment needed).\n\n**Key design decisions in the story:**\n- Contract written after every dispatch in `dispatchTaskWithResult()`, threaded through sequential flow and loop blocks\n- `changedFiles` extracted from `tool-complete` stream events during dispatch\n- `testResults: null` and `acceptanceCriteria: []` — extraction deferred to future stories\n- Graceful degradation: write failures logged as warnings, next task gets `null` contract\n- No new files — all changes in `workflow-engine.ts` and its test file\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:** None.\n\n**Workarounds applied:** None.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- AC #5 `changedFiles` extraction depends on drivers emitting `tool-complete` events with parseable tool names (Write/Edit). Not all drivers may do this consistently — the codex and opencode drivers parse CLI output, and tool name formats may vary. The story notes this as \"best-effort\" but the dev should verify actual `StreamEvent` shapes from each driver's test fixtures.\n- AC #7 (crash recovery with contracts) is implicitly covered by existing `isTaskCompleted` logic + atomic writes from 13-1, but the test needs to simulate the specific sequence carefully.\n- Changing `dispatchTask()` return type (Task 5) is a breaking change to its public signature. The story suggests returning `{ state, contract }` but `executeWorkflow()` and `executeLoopBlock()` both call `dispatchTask()` expecting `WorkflowState`. The dev needs to update all call sites.\n\n**Observations:**\n- This is the capstone story for Epic 13. After this, cross-framework execution is functionally complete.\n- The `previousOutputContract` parameter was pre-wired in story 13-2 specifically for this story, which simplifies the integration.\n- The `ToolCompleteEvent` type in `stream-parser.ts` has optional `name` and `args` fields, so the file path extraction for `changedFiles` will require parsing `args` (likely JSON-encoded tool input).\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Read: 5, Grep: 5, Glob: 4, Bash: 1, Write: 1, Edit: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run build` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a85c0fc0cb59f9618 (use SendMessage with to: 'a85c0fc0cb59f9618' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 64221\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 175342</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d2473842-56c4-49f2-ab43-68fabe9113bb","uuid":"839b4e5a-3e47-4597-bb86-ab769d2c9db4","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:48:56.857Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /create-story for story 13-3-cross-framework-workflow-execution. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append a verification tier tag using this decision tree:\n\n**Tier Decision Tree (append one `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tag per AC):**\n- `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests/linters/grep. No running app needed. Examples: 'function X exists', 'type Y is exported', 'test Z passes', 'file has <300 lines'.\n- `runtime-provable` — AC requires running the app locally and checking its behavior (CLI output, HTTP response, process lifecycle). No Docker stack needed. Examples: 'CLI prints usage when invoked with --help', 'server responds 200 on /health', 'process exits 0 on valid input'.\n- `environment-provable` — AC requires a full environment (Docker stack, database, observability, multi-service interaction). Examples: 'logs appear in VictoriaLogs', 'metrics are emitted to VictoriaMetrics', 'container communicates with service X'.\n- `escalate` — AC genuinely cannot be automated (requires physical hardware, paid external service, human visual judgment). This is rare. Examples: 'UI looks correct on mobile', 'payment processes successfully in production'.\n\nDefault to `test-provable` when unsure. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (errors, ambiguities in epic definition, missing context)\n- Workarounds applied (anything you did that felt hacky or suboptimal)\n- Risks identified (ACs that seem untestable, unclear requirements, missing dependencies)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy about this story)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls","agentId":"a85c0fc0cb59f9618","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-3-cross-framework-workflow-execution.md`.\n\n**Summary:** Created story 13-3 (Cross-Framework Workflow Execution) — the last story in Epic 13. It wires together the output contract write/read (13-1) and prompt injection (13-2) into the workflow engine's execution flow. 10 acceptance criteria, 8 tasks. All ACs tagged `test-provable` because they can be verified via build + unit tests with mocked drivers (no running app or environment needed).\n\n**Key design decisions in the story:**\n- Contract written after every dispatch in `dispatchTaskWithResult()`, threaded through sequential flow and loop blocks\n- `changedFiles` extracted from `tool-complete` stream events during dispatch\n- `testResults: null` and `acceptanceCriteria: []` — extraction deferred to future stories\n- Graceful degradation: write failures logged as warnings, next task gets `null` contract\n- No new files — all changes in `workflow-engine.ts` and its test file\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:** None.\n\n**Workarounds applied:** None.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- AC #5 `changedFiles` extraction depends on drivers emitting `tool-complete` events with parseable tool names (Write/Edit). Not all drivers may do this consistently — the codex and opencode drivers parse CLI output, and tool name formats may vary. The story notes this as \"best-effort\" but the dev should verify actual `StreamEvent` shapes from each driver's test fixtures.\n- AC #7 (crash recovery with contracts) is implicitly covered by existing `isTaskCompleted` logic + atomic writes from 13-1, but the test needs to simulate the specific sequence carefully.\n- Changing `dispatchTask()` return type (Task 5) is a breaking change to its public signature. The story suggests returning `{ state, contract }` but `executeWorkflow()` and `executeLoopBlock()` both call `dispatchTask()` expecting `WorkflowState`. The dev needs to update all call sites.\n\n**Observations:**\n- This is the capstone story for Epic 13. After this, cross-framework execution is functionally complete.\n- The `previousOutputContract` parameter was pre-wired in story 13-2 specifically for this story, which simplifies the integration.\n- The `ToolCompleteEvent` type in `stream-parser.ts` has optional `name` and `args` fields, so the file path extraction for `changedFiles` will require parsing `args` (likely JSON-encoded tool input).\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Read: 5, Grep: 5, Glob: 4, Bash: 1, Write: 1, Edit: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run build` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"}],"totalDurationMs":175342,"totalTokens":64221,"totalToolUseCount":25,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4668,"cache_read_input_tokens":58827,"output_tokens":725,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4668},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
