{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FHSDTrjAjFyv3LjGQSyTPC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<workflow>\n2\t  <critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n3\t  <critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {installed_path}/workflow.yaml</critical>\n4\t  <critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and language MUST be tailored to {user_skill_level}</critical>\n5\t  <critical>Generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n6\t\n7\t  <critical>🔥 YOU ARE AN ADVERSARIAL CODE REVIEWER - Find what's wrong or missing! 🔥</critical>\n8\t  <critical>Your purpose: Validate story file claims against actual implementation</critical>\n9\t  <critical>Challenge everything: Are tasks marked [x] actually done? Are ACs really implemented?</critical>\n10\t  <critical>Find 3-10 specific issues in every review minimum - no lazy \"looks good\" reviews - YOU are so much better than the dev agent\n11\t    that wrote this slop</critical>\n12\t  <critical>Read EVERY file in the File List - verify implementation against story requirements</critical>\n13\t  <critical>Tasks marked complete but not done = CRITICAL finding</critical>\n14\t  <critical>Acceptance Criteria not implemented = HIGH severity finding</critical>\n15\t  <critical>Do not review files that are not part of the application's source code. Always exclude the _bmad/ and _bmad-output/ folders from the review. Always exclude IDE and CLI configuration folders like .cursor/ and .windsurf/ and .claude/</critical>\n16\t\n17\t\n18\t  <step n=\"1\" goal=\"Load story and discover changes\">\n19\t    <action>Use provided {{story_path}} or ask user which story file to review</action>\n20\t    <action>Read COMPLETE story file</action>\n21\t    <action>Set {{story_key}} = extracted key from filename (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication.md\" → \"1-2-user-authentication\") or story\n22\t      metadata</action>\n23\t    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Agent Record → File List, Change Log</action>\n24\t\n25\t    <!-- Discover actual changes via git -->\n26\t    <action>Check if git repository detected in current directory</action>\n27\t    <check if=\"git repository exists\">\n28\t      <action>Run `git status --porcelain` to find uncommitted changes</action>\n29\t      <action>Run `git diff --name-only` to see modified files</action>\n30\t      <action>Run `git diff --cached --name-only` to see staged files</action>\n31\t      <action>Compile list of actually changed files from git output</action>\n32\t    </check>\n33\t\n34\t    <!-- Cross-reference story File List vs git reality -->\n35\t    <action>Compare story's Dev Agent Record → File List with actual git changes</action>\n36\t    <action>Note discrepancies:\n37\t      - Files in git but not in story File List\n38\t      - Files in story File List but no git changes\n39\t      - Missing documentation of what was actually changed\n40\t    </action>\n41\t\n42\t    <invoke-protocol name=\"discover_inputs\" />\n43\t    <action>Load {project_context} for coding standards (if exists)</action>\n44\t  </step>\n45\t\n46\t  <step n=\"2\" goal=\"Build review attack plan\">\n47\t    <action>Extract ALL Acceptance Criteria from story</action>\n48\t    <action>Extract ALL Tasks/Subtasks with completion status ([x] vs [ ])</action>\n49\t    <action>From Dev Agent Record → File List, compile list of claimed changes</action>\n50\t\n51\t    <action>Create review plan:\n52\t      1. **AC Validation**: Verify each AC is actually implemented\n53\t      2. **Task Audit**: Verify each [x] task is really done\n54\t      3. **Code Quality**: Security, performance, maintainability\n55\t      4. **Test Quality**: Real tests vs placeholder bullshit\n56\t    </action>\n57\t  </step>\n58\t\n59\t  <step n=\"3\" goal=\"Execute adversarial review\">\n60\t    <critical>VALIDATE EVERY CLAIM - Check git reality vs story claims</critical>\n61\t\n62\t    <!-- Git vs Story Discrepancies -->\n63\t    <action>Review git vs story File List discrepancies:\n64\t      1. **Files changed but not in story File List** → MEDIUM finding (incomplete documentation)\n65\t      2. **Story lists files but no git changes** → HIGH finding (false claims)\n66\t      3. **Uncommitted changes not documented** → MEDIUM finding (transparency issue)\n67\t    </action>\n68\t\n69\t    <!-- Use combined file list: story File List + git discovered files -->\n70\t    <action>Create comprehensive review file list from story File List and git changes</action>\n71\t\n72\t    <!-- AC Validation -->\n73\t    <action>For EACH Acceptance Criterion:\n74\t      1. Read the AC requirement\n75\t      2. Search implementation files for evidence\n76\t      3. Determine: IMPLEMENTED, PARTIAL, or MISSING\n77\t      4. If MISSING/PARTIAL → HIGH SEVERITY finding\n78\t    </action>\n79\t\n80\t    <!-- Task Completion Audit -->\n81\t    <action>For EACH task marked [x]:\n82\t      1. Read the task description\n83\t      2. Search files for evidence it was actually done\n84\t      3. **CRITICAL**: If marked [x] but NOT DONE → CRITICAL finding\n85\t      4. Record specific proof (file:line)\n86\t    </action>\n87\t\n88\t    <!-- Code Quality Deep Dive -->\n89\t    <action>For EACH file in comprehensive review list:\n90\t      1. **Security**: Look for injection risks, missing validation, auth issues\n91\t      2. **Performance**: N+1 queries, inefficient loops, missing caching\n92\t      3. **Error Handling**: Missing try/catch, poor error messages\n93\t      4. **Code Quality**: Complex functions, magic numbers, poor naming\n94\t      5. **Test Quality**: Are tests real assertions or placeholders?\n95\t    </action>\n96\t\n97\t    <check if=\"total_issues_found lt 3\">\n98\t      <critical>NOT LOOKING HARD ENOUGH - Find more problems!</critical>\n99\t      <action>Re-examine code for:\n100\t        - Edge cases and null handling\n101\t        - Architecture violations\n102\t        - Documentation gaps\n103\t        - Integration issues\n104\t        - Dependency problems\n105\t        - Git commit message quality (if applicable)\n106\t      </action>\n107\t      <action>Find at least 3 more specific, actionable issues</action>\n108\t    </check>\n109\t  </step>\n110\t\n111\t  <step n=\"4\" goal=\"Present findings and fix them\">\n112\t    <action>Categorize findings: HIGH (must fix), MEDIUM (should fix), LOW (nice to fix)</action>\n113\t    <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = 0</action>\n114\t    <action>Set {{action_count}} = 0</action>\n115\t\n116\t    <output>**🔥 CODE REVIEW FINDINGS, {user_name}!**\n117\t\n118\t      **Story:** {{story_file}}\n119\t      **Git vs Story Discrepancies:** {{git_discrepancy_count}} found\n120\t      **Issues Found:** {{high_count}} High, {{medium_count}} Medium, {{low_count}} Low\n121\t\n122\t      ## 🔴 CRITICAL ISSUES\n123\t      - Tasks marked [x] but not actually implemented\n124\t      - Acceptance Criteria not implemented\n125\t      - Story claims files changed but no git evidence\n126\t      - Security vulnerabilities\n127\t\n128\t      ## 🟡 MEDIUM ISSUES\n129\t      - Files changed but not documented in story File List\n130\t      - Uncommitted changes not tracked\n131\t      - Performance problems\n132\t      - Poor test coverage/quality\n133\t      - Code maintainability issues\n134\t\n135\t      ## 🟢 LOW ISSUES\n136\t      - Code style improvements\n137\t      - Documentation gaps\n138\t      - Git commit message quality\n139\t    </output>\n140\t\n141\t    <ask>What should I do with these issues?\n142\t\n143\t      1. **Fix them automatically** - I'll update the code and tests\n144\t      2. **Create action items** - Add to story Tasks/Subtasks for later\n145\t      3. **Show me details** - Deep dive into specific issues\n146\t\n147\t      Choose [1], [2], or specify which issue to examine:</ask>\n148\t\n149\t    <check if=\"user chooses 1\">\n150\t      <action>Fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues in the code</action>\n151\t      <action>Add/update tests as needed</action>\n152\t      <action>Update File List in story if files changed</action>\n153\t      <action>Update story Dev Agent Record with fixes applied</action>\n154\t      <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = number of HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed</action>\n155\t      <action>Set {{action_count}} = 0</action>\n156\t    </check>\n157\t\n158\t    <check if=\"user chooses 2\">\n159\t      <action>Add \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection to Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n160\t      <action>For each issue: `- [ ] [AI-Review][Severity] Description [file:line]`</action>\n161\t      <action>Set {{action_count}} = number of action items created</action>\n162\t      <action>Set {{fixed_count}} = 0</action>\n163\t    </check>\n164\t\n165\t    <check if=\"user chooses 3\">\n166\t      <action>Show detailed explanation with code examples</action>\n167\t      <action>Return to fix decision</action>\n168\t    </check>\n169\t  </step>\n170\t\n171\t  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:review-enforcement -->\n172\t## Codeharness Review Gates\n173\t\n174\t### Verification\n175\t- [ ] Proof document exists and passes codeharness verify\n176\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria have evidence in proof document\n177\t\n178\t### Coverage\n179\t- [ ] No coverage regression in changed files\n180\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:review-enforcement -->\n181\t\n182\t  <step n=\"5\" goal=\"Update story status and sync sprint tracking\">\n183\t    <!-- Determine new status based on review outcome -->\n184\t    <check if=\"all HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed AND all ACs implemented\">\n185\t      <action>Set {{new_status}} = \"done\"</action>\n186\t      <action>Update story Status field to \"done\"</action>\n187\t    </check>\n188\t    <check if=\"HIGH or MEDIUM issues remain OR ACs not fully implemented\">\n189\t      <action>Set {{new_status}} = \"in-progress\"</action>\n190\t      <action>Update story Status field to \"in-progress\"</action>\n191\t    </check>\n192\t    <action>Save story file</action>\n193\t\n194\t    <!-- Determine sprint tracking status -->\n195\t    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file exists\">\n196\t      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"enabled\"</action>\n197\t    </check>\n198\t    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file does NOT exist\">\n199\t      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"no-sprint-tracking\"</action>\n200\t    </check>\n201\t\n202\t    <!-- Sync sprint-status.yaml when story status changes (only if sprint tracking enabled) -->\n203\t    <check if=\"{{current_sprint_status}} != 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n204\t      <action>Load the FULL file: {sprint_status}</action>\n205\t      <action>Find development_status key matching {{story_key}}</action>\n206\t\n207\t      <check if=\"{{new_status}} == 'done'\">\n208\t        <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"done\"</action>\n209\t        <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure</action>\n210\t        <output>✅ Sprint status synced: {{story_key}} → done</output>\n211\t      </check>\n212\t\n213\t      <check if=\"{{new_status}} == 'in-progress'\">\n214\t        <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"in-progress\"</action>\n215\t        <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure</action>\n216\t        <output>🔄 Sprint status synced: {{story_key}} → in-progress</output>\n217\t      </check>\n218\t\n219\t      <check if=\"story key not found in sprint status\">\n220\t        <output>⚠️ Story file updated, but sprint-status sync failed: {{story_key}} not found in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n221\t      </check>\n222\t    </check>\n223\t\n224\t    <check if=\"{{current_sprint_status}} == 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n225\t      <output>ℹ️ Story status updated (no sprint tracking configured)</output>\n226\t    </check>\n227\t\n228\t    <output>**✅ Review Complete!**\n229\t\n230\t      **Story Status:** {{new_status}}\n231\t      **Issues Fixed:** {{fixed_count}}\n232\t      **Action Items Created:** {{action_count}}\n233\t\n234\t      {{#if new_status == \"done\"}}Code review complete!{{else}}Address the action items and continue development.{{/if}}\n235\t    </output>\n236\t  </step>\n237\t\n238\t</workflow>"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkXPMmo5ukZsEWidXQjyr7","session_id":"d2473842-56c4-49f2-ab43-68fabe9113bb","uuid":"d4251247-6d7a-41df-a65b-898cc02da934","timestamp":"2026-04-03T10:57:54.054Z"}
