{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JHFDmM8w4nBmJSwcfgKh7r","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 13.3: Cross-Framework Workflow Execution\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want to run a workflow where implement uses claude-code and verify uses codex,\n11\tso that verification is structurally independent from implementation.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a workflow with `implement: { driver: claude-code }` and `verify: { driver: codex }`\n16\t   **When** `executeWorkflow()` completes the implement task\n17\t   **Then** the workflow engine writes an `OutputContract` JSON file to `.codeharness/contracts/{taskName}-{storyId}.json` via `writeOutputContract()`\n18\t   **And** the contract's `taskName`, `storyId`, `driver`, `model`, `timestamp`, and `duration_ms` fields are populated from the dispatch context\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** the implement task has completed and its output contract exists on disk\n22\t   **When** the workflow engine dispatches the next task (e.g., verify)\n23\t   **Then** it reads the previous task's contract via `readOutputContract()` and passes it as `previousOutputContract` to `dispatchTask()`\n24\t   **And** the contract context is injected into the verify task's prompt via `buildPromptWithContractContext()`\n25\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t3. **Given** sequential flow steps `[\"create-story\", \"implement\", \"verify\"]`\n28\t   **When** the engine processes them in order\n29\t   **Then** after `create-story` completes, an output contract is written\n30\t   **And** `implement` receives the contract from `create-story` as prompt context\n31\t   **And** after `implement` completes, its own output contract is written\n32\t   **And** `verify` receives the contract from `implement` as prompt context\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t4. **Given** a loop block `{ loop: [\"implement\", \"verify\"] }` with different drivers per task\n36\t   **When** the loop executes iteration N\n37\t   **Then** after `implement` completes, its output contract is written\n38\t   **And** `verify` receives the output contract from `implement` as prompt context\n39\t   **And** on the next iteration, `implement` receives the output contract from the previous iteration's `verify` task\n40\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n41\t\n42\t5. **Given** the workflow engine dispatches a task and the driver yields `StreamEvent` objects\n43\t   **When** the dispatch completes\n44\t   **Then** the `OutputContract.output` field is set to the accumulated text from `text` events\n45\t   **And** `OutputContract.cost_usd` is set from the `result` event's cost (or `null` if not reported)\n46\t   **And** `OutputContract.changedFiles` is populated from `tool-complete` events for Write/Edit tools (or empty array if none)\n47\t   **And** `OutputContract.testResults` is `null` (test result extraction is not implemented in this story)\n48\t   **And** `OutputContract.acceptanceCriteria` is an empty array (AC extraction is not implemented in this story)\n49\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n50\t\n51\t6. **Given** the first task in a workflow (no previous task)\n52\t   **When** the engine dispatches it\n53\t   **Then** `previousOutputContract` is `null` and no contract injection occurs\n54\t   **And** the prompt is the base prompt unchanged\n55\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n56\t\n57\t7. **Given** the engine crashes after writing the output contract but before dispatching the next task\n58\t   **When** the engine resumes (NFR18: idempotent re-run)\n59\t   **Then** the previously-written output contract is still on disk (atomic writes from story 13-1)\n60\t   **And** the next task correctly reads it on resume\n61\t   **And** the completed task is skipped (existing crash recovery via `isTaskCompleted`)\n62\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n63\t\n64\t8. **Given** a `writeOutputContract()` call fails (e.g., disk full)\n65\t   **When** the error occurs\n66\t   **Then** the engine logs a warning but does NOT abort the workflow\n67\t   **And** the next task receives `null` as `previousOutputContract` (graceful degradation)\n68\t   **And** the workflow continues executing subsequent tasks\n69\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n70\t\n71\t9. **Given** the contract directory `.codeharness/contracts/` does not exist\n72\t   **When** the engine writes the first output contract\n73\t   **Then** the directory is created automatically (by `writeOutputContract()`'s `mkdirSync` with `recursive: true`)\n74\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n75\t\n76\t10. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n77\t    **When** the build completes\n78\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n79\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n80\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n81\t\n82\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n83\t\n84\t- [x] Task 1: Add output contract writing to `dispatchTaskWithResult()` in `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` (AC: #1, #5, #8, #9)\n85\t  - [x] Import `writeOutputContract` and `readOutputContract` from `./agents/output-contract.js`\n86\t  - [x] After step 12 (record trace ID) and before step 13 (write state to disk), construct an `OutputContract` from dispatch context:\n87\t    - `version: 1`\n88\t    - `taskName` from the `taskName` parameter\n89\t    - `storyId` from the `storyKey` parameter\n90\t    - `driver` from `driverName`\n91\t    - `model` from the resolved `model`\n92\t    - `timestamp: new Date().toISOString()`\n93\t    - `cost_usd` from the `cost` variable (0 → null)\n94\t    - `duration_ms` computed from start/end timestamps around the dispatch\n95\t    - `changedFiles` extracted from `tool-complete` events during dispatch (Write/Edit tool names)\n96\t    - `testResults: null` (not extracted in this story)\n97\t    - `output` from the accumulated `output` string\n98\t    - `acceptanceCriteria: []` (not extracted in this story)\n99\t  - [x] Call `writeOutputContract(contract, join(projectDir, '.codeharness', 'contracts'))` inside a try/catch\n100\t  - [x] On write failure, call `warn()` with the error message — do NOT throw\n101\t  - [x] Return the contract from `dispatchTaskWithResult()` alongside `updatedState` and `output`\n102\t\n103\t- [x] Task 2: Track `changedFiles` from `StreamEvent` during dispatch (AC: #5)\n104\t  - [x] In the `for await (const event of driver.dispatch(...))` loop, track tool-complete events\n105\t  - [x] When `event.type === 'tool-complete'` and the tool name matches Write/Edit patterns, extract the file path from `event.args` or `event.name` and add to a `changedFiles: string[]` array\n106\t  - [x] Use the accumulated `changedFiles` when constructing the `OutputContract`\n107\t\n108\t- [x] Task 3: Wire contract passing in sequential flow execution in `executeWorkflow()` (AC: #2, #3, #6)\n109\t  - [x] Maintain a `lastOutputContract: OutputContract | null = null` variable across flow steps\n110\t  - [x] After each `dispatchTask()` call for sequential tasks, update `lastOutputContract` from the returned contract\n111\t  - [x] Pass `lastOutputContract` as `previousOutputContract` to the next `dispatchTask()` call\n112\t  - [x] Update `dispatchTask()` return type to include the output contract\n113\t\n114\t- [x] Task 4: Wire contract passing in loop block execution in `executeLoopBlock()` (AC: #4)\n115\t  - [x] Maintain a `lastOutputContract: OutputContract | null = null` variable across loop iterations\n116\t  - [x] After each task dispatch within the loop, update `lastOutputContract`\n117\t  - [x] Pass `lastOutputContract` as `previousOutputContract` to the next task dispatch\n118\t  - [x] The contract carries across iterations (verify's contract from iteration N is passed to implement in iteration N+1)\n119\t\n120\t- [x] Task 5: Update `dispatchTask()` and `dispatchTaskWithResult()` signatures (AC: #1, #2)\n121\t  - [x] Change `dispatchTaskWithResult()` to return `{ updatedState, output, contract }` where `contract` is `OutputContract | null`\n122\t  - [x] Change `dispatchTask()` to return `{ state: WorkflowState; contract: OutputContract | null }`\n123\t\n124\t- [x] Task 6: Add timing measurement to `dispatchTaskWithResult()` (AC: #1, #5)\n125\t  - [x] Record `const startMs = Date.now()` before the dispatch loop\n126\t  - [x] Compute `duration_ms = Date.now() - startMs` after the dispatch loop\n127\t  - [x] Use this for `OutputContract.duration_ms`\n128\t\n129\t- [x] Task 7: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#10)\n130\t  - [x] In `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`:\n131\t    - [x] Test: `dispatchTaskWithResult` writes output contract to `.codeharness/contracts/`\n132\t    - [x] Test: `dispatchTaskWithResult` returns the written contract\n133\t    - [x] Test: sequential flow passes contract from task N to task N+1 via `previousOutputContract`\n134\t    - [x] Test: first task in flow gets `null` as `previousOutputContract`\n135\t    - [x] Test: loop block passes contract between tasks within an iteration\n136\t    - [x] Test: loop block carries contract across iterations\n137\t    - [x] Test: contract `output` field contains accumulated text events\n138\t    - [x] Test: contract `cost_usd` is populated from result event cost\n139\t    - [x] Test: contract `changedFiles` is populated from tool-complete events for Write/Edit\n140\t    - [x] Test: write failure is caught and logged, next task gets `null` contract\n141\t    - [x] Test: contract directory is created if it does not exist\n142\t\n143\t- [x] Task 8: Verify build and tests (AC: #10)\n144\t  - [x] Run `npm run build` — zero TypeScript errors\n145\t  - [x] Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, no regressions\n146\t\n147\t## Dev Notes\n148\t\n149\t### Architecture Compliance\n150\t\n151\tThis story implements Epic 4, Story 4.3 (mapped to sprint Epic 13, Story 13-3) \"Cross-Framework Workflow Execution\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n152\t- **FR16:** System can execute a workflow where consecutive tasks use different drivers\n153\t- **FR17:** System can serialize a task's output contract to a structured JSON file after task completion\n154\t- **FR19:** System can pass acceptance criteria, changed file lists, and test results across framework boundaries via output contracts\n155\t- **FR20:** System can execute verification tasks on a different framework than implementation tasks\n156\t- **NFR18:** Workflow engine must be idempotent for re-runs — resume from last completed task\n157\t\n158\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n159\t- **Decision 3 (Output Contract Format):** JSON files in `.codeharness/contracts/{taskName}-{storyId}.json`. Written atomically.\n160\t- **Output Contract Population Pattern:** Engine populates contract after each dispatch. `changedFiles` from tool-complete events, `cost_usd` from `getLastCost()`, `output` from accumulated text. Fields not available are `null`.\n161\t- **Workflow Engine Boundary:** Engine writes/reads output contracts between tasks. Engine does NOT parse CLI output or know driver internals.\n162\t\n163\t### Implementation Strategy\n164\t\n165\tThis story wires together the pieces built in 13-1 (write/read) and 13-2 (prompt injection). The main integration points are:\n166\t\n167\t1. **After dispatch:** Construct `OutputContract` from dispatch context and write to disk via `writeOutputContract()`.\n168\t2. **Before dispatch:** Read the previous task's contract and pass it via `previousOutputContract` parameter (already wired in 13-2).\n169\t3. **Sequential flow:** Thread `lastOutputContract` through the flow step loop in `executeWorkflow()`.\n170\t4. **Loop blocks:** Thread `lastOutputContract` through the loop iteration in `executeLoopBlock()`.\n171\t\n172\tThe contract directory convention is `.codeharness/contracts/` under the project root. This matches the architecture spec and the state directory convention (`.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml`).\n173\t\n174\t**Changed file extraction:** During `driver.dispatch()`, `tool-complete` events with tool names like `Write`, `Edit`, `write_to_file`, `edit_file` etc. indicate file modifications. We extract file paths from these events. This is best-effort — not all drivers emit tool-complete events, and the file path format may vary.\n175\t\n176\t**Graceful degradation:** If `writeOutputContract()` fails (disk error, permissions), the engine logs a warning and continues. The next task simply gets no contract context. This is acceptable because the contract is an optimization (context passing), not a correctness requirement.\n177\t\n178\t### What Already Exists\n179\t\n180\t- `writeOutputContract()` / `readOutputContract()` — `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` (story 13-1)\n181\t- `buildPromptWithContractContext()` — `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` (story 13-2)\n182\t- `previousOutputContract` parameter — already on `dispatchTask()` and `dispatchTaskWithResult()` (wired in story 13-2)\n183\t- `OutputContract` interface — `src/lib/agents/types.ts` (lines 67-80)\n184\t- `DispatchOpts.outputContract` — field already exists in `types.ts` (line 94)\n185\t- Contract prompt injection — already wired in `dispatchTaskWithResult()` line 321\n186\t- `isTaskCompleted()` / `isLoopTaskCompleted()` — crash recovery already works (skips completed tasks on re-run)\n187\t- `warn()` — logging utility imported in `workflow-engine.ts`\n188\t- Mock infrastructure — `workflow-engine.test.ts` already mocks `getDriver`, `resolveModel`, `buildPromptWithContractContext`, etc.\n189\t\n190\t### What NOT to Do\n191\t\n192\t- Do NOT modify `output-contract.ts` — the write/read/format functions are complete from stories 13-1 and 13-2.\n193\t- Do NOT modify `types.ts` — `OutputContract`, `DispatchOpts`, `AgentDriver` are already defined.\n194\t- Do NOT modify any driver files — contract writing is engine-level, not driver-level.\n195\t- Do NOT implement test result extraction from driver output — that's a future enhancement. Set `testResults: null`.\n196\t- Do NOT implement acceptance criteria extraction — that's a future enhancement. Set `acceptanceCriteria: []`.\n197\t- Do NOT abort the workflow on contract write failure — graceful degradation is required (AC #8).\n198\t- Do NOT change the `dispatchTask()` public signature more than necessary — callers may depend on it returning `WorkflowState`. Consider returning an object `{ state, contract }` or adding the contract to a separate return path.\n199\t\n200\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n201\t\n202\tFrom story 13-2 (Output Contract Prompt Injection):\n203\t- `buildPromptWithContractContext()` already wired into `dispatchTaskWithResult()` at line 321.\n204\t- `previousOutputContract` parameter already exists on both `dispatchTask()` and `dispatchTaskWithResult()`.\n205\t- 4526 tests passing across 168 test files, coverage 96.8%.\n206\t- `mockBuildPromptWithContractContext` already set up in workflow-engine tests.\n207\t\n208\tFrom story 13-1 (Output Contract Schema & Serialization):\n209\t- `writeOutputContract()` creates directory recursively, writes atomically (.tmp → rename).\n210\t- `readOutputContract()` returns `null` when file doesn't exist.\n211\t- `assertSafeComponent()` validates taskName/storyId are safe filename components.\n212\t\n213\t### Testing Patterns\n214\t\n215\tFollow existing patterns in `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`:\n216\t- The test file already mocks all dependencies (driver factory, model resolver, workflow state, etc.).\n217\t- Add `mockWriteOutputContract` and `mockReadOutputContract` to the hoisted mocks.\n218\t- Mock `writeOutputContract` to capture the written contract for assertions.\n219\t- Mock `readOutputContract` to return a test contract when needed.\n220\t- For sequential flow tests, verify that `dispatchTask` calls pass the correct `previousOutputContract`.\n221\t- For loop block tests, verify contract threading across tasks and iterations.\n222\t- For error handling, mock `writeOutputContract` to throw and verify `warn()` is called.\n223\t\n224\tThe `mockDriverDispatch` already yields `StreamEvent` objects — extend it to yield `tool-complete` events for Write/Edit to test `changedFiles` extraction.\n225\t\n226\t### Project Structure Notes\n227\t\n228\tFiles to CREATE:\n229\t- None (all changes go in existing files)\n230\t\n231\tFiles to MODIFY:\n232\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — add contract writing after dispatch, thread contracts through sequential and loop flows, track changedFiles from tool-complete events\n233\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — add tests for contract writing, threading, graceful degradation\n234\t\n235\tFiles NOT to modify:\n236\t- `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` — complete from stories 13-1 and 13-2\n237\t- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — OutputContract and DispatchOpts already defined\n238\t- Any driver files — contract management is engine-level\n239\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — output_contract field on tasks is for schema-level config\n240\t- `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` — state management is already complete\n241\t\n242\t### References\n243\t\n244\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 4.3: Cross-Framework Workflow Execution]\n245\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Decision 3: Output Contract Format]\n246\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Output Contract Population Pattern]\n247\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md — FR16, FR17, FR19, FR20, NFR18]\n248\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — OutputContract interface]\n249\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts — writeOutputContract, readOutputContract, buildPromptWithContractContext]\n250\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — dispatchTask(), dispatchTaskWithResult(), executeWorkflow(), executeLoopBlock()]\n251\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization.md — story 13-1 context]\n252\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection.md — story 13-2 context]\n253\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01LTZ8mWkxebmEYkywZErtdF","session_id":"d2473842-56c4-49f2-ab43-68fabe9113bb","uuid":"db874def-322d-4efd-b706-e57b3638b2c9","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:03:04.446Z"}
